Convert to Market Data Tibble

Source: R/market_tbl.R
as_market_tbl.Rd

Converts various data formats to a standardized market_tbl object.

Usage

as_market_tbl(data, symbol_col = "symbol", datetime_col = "datetime", ...)

Arguments

data

A data frame or tibble with market data

symbol_col

Name of the column containing symbols (default: "symbol")

datetime_col

Name of the column containing timestamps (default: "datetime")

...

Additional arguments passed to market_tbl()

Value

A market_tbl object

Examples

# Convert a regular data frame
df <- data.frame(
  symbol = rep("AAPL", 3),
  datetime = as.POSIXct(c("2024-01-01", "2024-01-02", "2024-01-03")),
  open = c(150, 151, 152),
  high = c(152, 153, 154),
  low = c(149, 150, 151),
  close = c(151, 152, 153),
  volume = c(1e6, 1.1e6, 1.2e6)
)

market_data <- as_market_tbl(df)
